m_q.target_metric: Mean Absolute Error (MAE) of NOAA SWPC's 3-day AP forecast made on March 9, 2025 for the period March 10-12, 2025
sub_questions: What are the forecasted AP values for March 10-12, 2025 from the March 9 forecast?
What are the actual AP values for March 10-12, 2025?
How to calculate MAE from forecast vs actual AP values?

schema_conflicts: All files have identical column names but different data values
Column names are not descriptive (':Product:' and filename columns)

scale_issues: AP values appear to be in standard AP index units (typically 0-400)
cross_source_conflicts: Need to verify that all files use same AP measurement scale and methodology

format_notes: Files contain mixed data types in same column
Some rows contain AP forecast ranges (e.g., 'Mar,025-020-012')
First column appears to be row identifiers or metadata

constraints: Forecast period must be exactly March 10-12, 2025
Forecast must be from March 9, 2025 issuance
AP values must be non-negative integers
derived_filters: Extract only rows containing AP forecast/actual values
Filter out metadata rows (UTC, month names, blank rows)
statistical_tests: Check for missing values in forecast/actual pairs
output_format_requirements: MAE should be calculated as: MAE = mean(|forecast - actual|) for March 10-12
Result should be a single numeric value with appropriate precision
